TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {38380=Rebecca Burkhardt and Cynthia Goatley began their work on a musical, “Writing Just Ann, A Musical about the Life and Times of Former Governor of Texas, Ann Richards,” in 2008. Spending two summers and a fall in Austin allowed Burkhardt and Goatley to gather volumes of material. In order to condense this large amount of material into a workable size for a musical theatre piece, they began by drawing on sketch paper clusters of songs and scenes for the musical. A first draft of the piece was read and sung in May by students, faculty and community members, so the authors could hear what needed to be revised. A second draft is now in progress., 26556=The Sixth Annual Graduate Student Symposium is Thursday, April 4. Learn about the types of presentations at the Symposium, benefits of participation, helpful hints for your presentation or performance, judging criteria, prize information and how to begin to prepare for the event.}
